      "text": [
        " مَا اسْتَشْفَى النَّاسُ بِمِثْلِ الْعَسَلِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Abu Nasr, from Hammad Bin Usman, from Muhammad Bin Sowqa, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The people are not healed with the likes of (healing with) the honey’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ibn abu Nasr from Hammad ibn ‘Uthaman from Muhammad ibn Sawqah who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘People are not cured as good as with honey.’” "
        ]
      }
